rule.Name: BadRecursiveInvocationRule
rule.problem: This method, or property, invokes itself recursively in a suspcious way.
rule.solution: Ensure that an exit condition exists to terminate recursion.

rule.Name: CheckNewExceptionWithoutThrowingRule
rule.problem: This method creates an exception that is never throwed nor returned to the caller.
rule.solution: Make sure the exception is required, throw it (if it is) or remove it (if not).

rule.Name: CloneMethodShouldNotReturnNullRule
rule.problem: The implementation ICloneable.Clone () seems to return null in some circumstances.
rule.solution: Return an appropriate object instead of returning null.

rule.Name: ConstructorShouldNotCallVirtualMethodsRule
rule.problem: Some constructors calls virtual methods which won't be known before runtime.
rule.solution: Avoid calling virtual methods from constructors or seal the the type.
